at parties.

245
00:16:04,370 --> 00:16:08,204
lt was good of you to come.
Don't you look beautiful!

246
00:16:08,273 --> 00:16:11,174
- You know Bonnie Sherow.
- Of course. How are you?

247
00:16:11,243 --> 00:16:14,303
- Tri-Star, right?
- She's at the studio.

248
00:16:14,380 --> 00:16:19,682
That's what l meant. Bring Mr. Mill
a martini. And, Bonnie?

249
00:16:19,752 --> 00:16:22,744
- l'll take a Ramlosa.
- l'll have a martini.

250
00:16:25,090 --> 00:16:28,025
Rod Steiger's here.

251
00:16:28,093 --> 00:16:30,027
Talk to him about the Rudolph project.

252
00:16:30,095 --> 00:16:34,464
He's not that hot on it,
but see if you can get him to read it.

253
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:37,263
You know who's here? Harry Belafonte.
Harry?

254
00:16:37,336 --> 00:16:39,964
Come and say hello, will you?

255
00:16:42,041 --> 00:16:44,703
- Griffin Mill.
- Hi. Good to see you.

256
00:16:44,777 --> 00:16:47,644
Bonnie Sherow.
She's gaga over you.

257
00:16:47,713 --> 00:16:51,444
