the Nelson Mandela Courage Award.

258
00:16:52,751 --> 00:16:56,482
Who was the villain in Ghostbusters?

259
00:16:56,555 --> 00:16:59,422
You got me there.

260
00:16:59,491 --> 00:17:01,516
l got this--

261
00:17:03,529 --> 00:17:08,262
l got this postcard.
Harassment kind of stuff.

262
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:11,097
What are you talking about?

263
00:17:12,838 --> 00:17:15,136
lt's some writer
l must've brushed off.

264
00:17:15,207 --> 00:17:18,404
Get something to eat.
There's lovely stuff over there.

265
00:17:18,477 --> 00:17:20,672
We will in a few minutes.

266
00:17:20,746 --> 00:17:22,441
Your hands are as cold as mine.

267
00:17:22,514 --> 00:17:25,278
Would you like one of these?

268
00:17:25,350 --> 00:17:27,511
l don't think l do.

269
00:17:27,586 --> 00:17:30,316
Are you talking about threats?

270
00:17:30,389 --> 00:17:32,949
No. Yes.

271
00:17:33,025 --> 00:17:36,392
l don't know.
He's pissed off.

272
00:17:36,462 --> 00:17:40,831
l thought writers were your long suit.
You're the writer's executive.

273
00:17:40,899 --> 00:17:43,129
Are you pitching me a dream?

274
00:17:43,202 --> 00:17:47,696
- You don't sound sincerely interested.
- lt depends how good the dream is.

275
00:17:49,174 --> 00:17:50,971
Levy's here.

276
00:17:54,379 --> 00:17:59,214
- Dick, what's he doing here?
- Goldblum? He's a friend.

277
00:17:59,284 --> 00:18:02,185
- No, Larry Levy.
- He came with Sally.

278
00:18:02,254 --> 00:18:04,484
What's going on with my job?

279
00:18:04,556 --> 00:18:07,821
